title: Grateful Dead Live at Jai-Alai Fronton on 1974-06-22
lineage: Master Cassettes > cassettes re-shelled > nak dragon>hd-p2 24/96 > cd wave > flac
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Deal, Me And Bobby McGee, Scarlet Begonias, Jack Straw, Loose Lucy, Mexicali Blues, Sugaree, The Race is On, It Must Have Been The Roses, Playin' In The Band

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Me & My Uncle, Ship of Fools, El Paso, Eyes Of The World-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Florida Dead! Thanx Jerry and Rob.  Decent sounding aud.  Show average by the standards of the day.  Good Playing/Band.  I am playing Eyes thru Sugar Mags on my radio show tonight.  Peace

providence flip flop jerry, how often did you see the dead do a short chinacat and long rider one show and the opposite another? check out providence 6/26/74. nice job recording, enjoyed it throughout. I caught the bus 7/6/87 but love listening to these jems.

Dancing on the stage Went to the Grateful Dead’s luau at the coconut grove hotel prior and was dancing on the stage next to Jerry at this show with my friend , just the two of us . Wish I had photos . Fabulous awesome show .  Jerry Moore RIP taped this show . We were travelin with him and Les K for part of the 1974 East coast summer tour They ran Dead Relix magazine at the time . We crashed in their room on the floor at the wonderful  coconut grove hotel in Miami Beach. Later Jerry Moore and my friend Louis Falanga another well known taper became friends . I’ve got Jerry Moore’s recording given to Louis of this show . Not soundboard but audience.
